1
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:23,041
( wind howling )

2
00:00:23,125 --> 00:00:26,291
- ( explosions )

3
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:33,125
- ( clanking )

4
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:41,416
- HEY! WHAT THE HELL YOU JUST
STANDING AROUND FOR,

5
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,833
YOU LITTLE BRAT?

6
00:00:46,958 --> 00:00:48,333
YOU THE SAD LITTLE ORPHAN BOY

7
00:00:48,416 --> 00:00:50,708
OF ONE OF THESE HIGH
AND MIGHTY ROLAND SOLDIERS,

8
00:00:50,791 --> 00:00:52,541
OR THE BOUGHT-AND-PAID FOR
PLEASURE CHILD

9
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:54,416
OF SOME ESTABULIAN FOP?

10
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,333
TELL ME YOUR NAME, KID!

11
00:00:56,416 --> 00:00:59,000
- UH, IT'S RYNER LUTE.

12
00:00:59,083 --> 00:01:00,208
- LOUDER NEXT TIME!

13
00:01:03,416 --> 00:01:05,291
FOLKS CALL ME TALROM.

14
00:01:05,375 --> 00:01:08,208
ACT LIKE A DEADWEIGHT AROUND
HERE, THIS IS WHAT YOU GET.

15
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:10,125
GOT IT, RYNER LUTE?

16
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:13,666
SHOW ME YOU UNDERSTAND
BY GETTIN' OFF YOUR ASS.

17
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:16,916
FROM NOW ON, WORK LIKE
YOUR LIFE DEPENDS ON IT.

18
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,708
BECAUSE IT DOES.

19
00:01:39,083 --> 00:01:40,666
- ( theme song playing )

20
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:14,916
- IRIS JAW-BREAKER!

21
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,291
- HEY, COME ON!

22
00:03:16,375 --> 00:03:17,750
DO YOU THINK YOU COULD
STOP TRYING TO HIT ME

23
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:20,250
EVERY TIME I'M
WITHIN FIVE FEET?

24
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:21,875
- HANDS OFF, VILE THING!

25
00:03:21,958 --> 00:03:24,958
I DON'T INTEND TO HAVE MY
VIRTUE FOREVER RUINED BY YOU!

26
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:27,833
- OH, RIGHT... FERRIS PUT
THE IDEA IN YOUR HEAD

27
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,416
THAT THE SLIGHTEST BRUSH
WITH YOURS TRULY

28
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,083
BURDENS A GIRL WITH CHILD...

29
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:34,333
RELAX OKAY, NOT EVERYTHING
SHE SAYS IS ABSOLUTELY TRUE.

30
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:36,833
( gasps )

31
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:40,250
- YET, YOU CLUTCH HER ARM
FOR NO REASON I CAN DISCERN.

32
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:42,375
- LOOK I'M NOT ABDUCTING,
IMPREGNATING

33
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:43,416
OR OTHERWISE CORRUPTING
YOUR PRECIOUS BABY SISTER

34
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,291
IN ANY WAY SHAPE OR FORM, OKAY?

35
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:48,125
YOU KNOW,

36
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:49,833
I THINK IT SPEAKS TO HOW FAR
WE'VE COME IN THIS RELATIONSHIP

37
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:51,750
THAT I'M ACTUALLY STARTING TO
FEEL YOUR EYES BORE A HOLE

38
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,416
IN THE BACK OF MY HEAD.

39
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,291
- BIG SISTER FERRIS!

40
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:56,583
- HOW LOVELY TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

41
00:03:56,666 --> 00:03:58,541
SO THERE WAS NO
MISADVENTURE EN ROUTE?

42
00:03:58,625 --> 00:04:00,458
- NOPE! I MISSED YOU,

43
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:02,875
SO I DIDN'T WASTE A
SINGLE MOMENT GETTING HERE.

44
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:06,625
I DO GOOD? TELL ME, I...

45
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:09,541
- YOU DID.
- HEY, EASY!

46
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,666
- OH, I'M SORRY.
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

47
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:12,875
IRIS IS ALL WORKED UP,

48
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:14,875
SO I'M JUST COAXING
HER INTO A LITTLE NAP.

49
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:16,666
- THIS IS THE WAY YOU COAX HER?

50
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:17,958
- ( chuckles )

51
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:19,958
COME ON, MY BROTHER
DID THE SAME THING FOR ME

52
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:22,791
WHEN I WAS A CHILD,
NOW I DO IT FOR HER.

53
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:25,708
- HOW THE HELL'D YOU
SURVIVE BEING A KID?

54
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:28,083
- AH, EXCELLENT...

55
00:04:28,166 --> 00:04:29,458
WYNNIT TEA HOUSE DANGO

56
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:31,666
WILL MAKE THIS A VERY
GOOD MORNING INDEED.

57
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:42,125
- I DON'T BELIEVE THIS. YOUR
LITTLE SISTER'S CRUMPLED IN

58
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:45,291
A HEAP ON THE FLOOR AND YOU'RE
CHOWING DOWN ON PREMIUM DANGO.

59
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:51,791
- IRIS HAS REACHED THEM
BY NOW, HOPEFULLY...

60
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,958
IF IT WASN'T TOO LATE.

61
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:58,458
- YOU'RE SO RIGHT!
THIS STUFF IS GOOD!

62
00:04:58,541 --> 00:04:59,833
- SEE?

63
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:01,625
- YOU'VE BOTH BEEN HOARDING
OVER THAT DANGO LIKE MAD

64
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:03,125
ALL MORNING.

65
00:05:03,208 --> 00:05:06,166
SURELY THAT'S NOT THE ONLY
REASON YOU CAME HERE, IRIS...

66
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:10,083
- HUH? WELL NO...
I MEAN... I THINK...

67
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:11,875
- OF COURSE!
I BROUGHT A LETTER!

68
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:13,375
- YOU MEAN FROM SION?

69
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:15,250
- YEAH, I CARRIED IT HERE ALL
THE WAY FROM THE PALACE...

70
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,041
HIS MAJESTY TOLD ME
TO DELIVER IT

71
00:05:17,125 --> 00:05:19,666
AS SOON AS HUMANLY POSSIBLE,
IF NOT FASTER...

72
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:22,958
THERE WAS SOME REALLY IMPORTANT
INFORMATION IN IT, SO...

73
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:26,541
- WELL HERE, LET ME GET IT.
- IF YOU MUST.

74
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:28,833
- HUH. OKAY, THAT'S
A LITTLE BIT WEIRD.

75
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:31,083
IF I TUCKED IT AWAY
WHERE IT'D BE SAFE...

76
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:33,166
'CAUSE OF HOW
REALLY IMPORTANT IT WAS...

77
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,791
THEN WHERE'S THE STUPID THING
NOW? IT'S GOTTA BE IN HERE.

78
00:05:35,875 --> 00:05:37,041
- I DON'T SUPPOSE
HE ACTUALLY TOLD YOU

79
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:38,833
WHAT THE LETTER WAS ABOUT?

80
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:40,791
- UM, WELL...

81
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:44,500
I THINK IT WAS SOMETHING ABOUT
A BIG DRAGON BEING ON THE LOOSE.

82
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:46,166
- IS THAT A FACT?
- IS THAT A FACT?

83
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,500
- OH, YES. OF COURSE.

84
00:05:56,583 --> 00:05:58,833
THE WORTHLESS CREATURE
YOUR RELIC SET FREE.

85
00:05:58,916 --> 00:06:00,708
SION MUST WANT US TO TRACK
DOWN ITS WHEREABOUTS

86
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:02,333
AND TRY TO REIGN IT IN.

87
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:03,583
- AW MAN, WHY US?

88
00:06:03,666 --> 00:06:05,333
- THAT SOUNDS
ABOUT RIGHT, BUT...

89
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:07,333
I DON'T KNOW, I'M PRETTY SURE
THERE WAS SOMETHING ELSE

90
00:06:07,416 --> 00:06:09,166
REALLY CRUCIAL MIXED IN THERE...

91
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:10,375
- DON'T WORRY, SIS.

92
00:06:10,458 --> 00:06:12,583
WE'LL JUST FIGURE THINGS
OUT AS WE GO ALONG.

93
00:06:12,666 --> 00:06:15,291
- UH, WE WILL?

94
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:19,041
YOU KNOW, THAT SUDDENLY
SOUNDS LIKE A WONDERFUL IDEA...

95
00:06:19,125 --> 00:06:20,500
- ALRIGHT THEN.

96
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:22,625
GO BACK HOME AND TELL HIS
MAJESTY WE'LL DO AS HE ASKS.

97
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,583
- I'M ON THE JOB!

98
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:27,250
- ( yawning )

99
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:35,333
- Landlady: HMM. WHAT'S THIS?

100
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:37,750
"CONCERNING THE INCIDENT
LATELY REPORTED

101
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,958
"OF THE DRAGON THOUGHT
TO HAVE MATERIALIZED,

102
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:42,083
"CONJUNCTION WITH
THE RELIC UNEARTHED

103
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:43,583
IN THE FORESTS OF NELPHA..."

104
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:45,375
- Sion: WHILE NO FURTHER
SIGHTING OF THE CREATURE

105
00:06:45,458 --> 00:06:46,958
HAS COME TO LIGHT,

106
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:50,375
AN ALARMING NUMBER OF PEASANTS
FROM THE AREA HAVE BEEN KILLED.

107
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:53,666
ABANDON ALL ENDEAVORS TO
RETRIEVE THE RELIC IMMEDIATELY.

108
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:56,916
YOU ARE TO STAY CLEAR OF
THOSE FORESTS AT ALL COSTS.

109
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:11,125
- AN IDEAL SPOT FOR TEA.
- NOW THAT I CAN GET BEHIND.

110
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:13,208
I MOVE THAT WE LEAVE OFF
THE INVESTIGATION ENTIRELY

111
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:15,083
UNTIL WE'VE HAD
SOME REFRESHMENT.

112
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:24,875
- COULD THE DRAGON
HAVE DONE THIS?

113
00:07:24,958 --> 00:07:26,291
- Ferris: LET'S FIND OUT.

114
00:07:32,916 --> 00:07:37,750
RYNER, NO BLOOD
HAS BEEN SPILLED.

115
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,916
- YEAH. OTHERWISE WE'D HAVE
PROBABLY BEEN ABLE TO SMELL

116
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,625
THIS PLACE LONG
BEFORE WE FOUND IT.

117
00:07:41,708 --> 00:07:44,583
WHAT HAPPENED TO THESE PEOPLE?

118
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:47,916
- DOWN THERE.

119
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,875
- HELLO! EXCUSE US...

120
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:53,375
YOU'VE GOTTA BE KIDDING ME...

121
00:07:57,708 --> 00:07:59,083
- THERE'S SOMEONE COMING,

122
00:07:59,166 --> 00:08:01,166
IT LOOKS LIKE THE MYSTERIOUS
MISSIONARIES FROM NELPHA.

123
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,375
- WELL, OUR PATHS
CROSS YET AGAIN.

124
00:08:03,458 --> 00:08:05,958
WHAT A SERENDIPITOUS SURPRISE.

125
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:08,166
- WHAT ARE THE
TWO OF YOU DOING HERE?

126
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:11,375
- TRYING TO CATCH A GLIMPSE OF
THE RUMORED DRAGON, OF COURSE.

127
00:08:11,458 --> 00:08:12,541
- SUCH A UNIQUE SIGHT WOULD

128
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:14,916
ASSUREDLY LIGHT MY
WRITER'S QUILL AFIRE.

129
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,250
I IMAGINE A YOUNG PRINCESS

130
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:18,375
WRITHING IN ITS
CLUTCHES. HELPLESS...

131
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,916
- DOUBTLESS A KNIGHT IN
SHINING ARMOR THEN RIDES TO

132
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,166
HER RESCUE ON A GREAT
WHITE STEED AND FELLS THE

133
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:26,250
INFERNAL BEAST WITH A
FLICK OF HIS SHINING BLADE.

134
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,666
CLICHES LIKE THAT
BAR YOUR WRITING

135
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:30,166
FROM THE POPULAR MARKET,
YOU KNOW!

136
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:32,500
SO, WHAT DO YOU TWO
THINK'S GOING ON HERE?

137
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:34,750
- HEY, YOUR GUESS
IS AS GOOD AS MINE.

138
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:38,750
IT'S WEIRD THERE BEING NO
TELLTALE SIGNS OF BLOOD, BUT...

139
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:39,833
FERRIS?

140
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:41,291
- PERHAPS YOU TWO HAVE
YOUR OWN THEORY

141
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:43,291
AS TO THE NATURE OF THIS BEAST?

142
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:57,291
- YOUR EYE IS AS SHARP
AS YOUR DRESS, MY LADY.

143
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,958
- DID YOU KILL THEM?

144
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:02,000
- WE WERE INTERESTED IN THE
HIDDEN RICHES IN THE FORTRESS

145
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:04,208
FOR MUCH THE SAME
REASON YOU WERE,

146
00:09:04,291 --> 00:09:06,083
IF I'M NOT BEING TOO
VAGUE ON THE MATTER.

147
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:09,541
- SO YOU'RE OUT TO
FIND HERO RELICS AS WELL.

148
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:11,625
YOU'VE BEEN TAILING US
TO SAVE THE TROUBLE

149
00:09:11,708 --> 00:09:13,833
OF HAVING TO LOCATE
THEM YOURSELVES.

150
00:09:13,916 --> 00:09:16,041
- THAT ABOUT RIGHT?
- BRAVO.

151
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:18,500
WE CAN'T TAKE ALL THE CREDIT
FOR OUR SUCCESS, THOUGH,

152
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:20,791
THE TABOO BREAKER
SQUADRON HELPED IMMENSELY.

153
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:22,625
AS DID OF COURSE YOUR
INHERENT CLUMSINESS

154
00:09:22,708 --> 00:09:24,750
IN LEAVING THIS
RELIC FOR US TO FIND.

155
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,583
WE WERE EXTREMELY LUCKY...

156
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:27,625
IT WAS, AS THE
OLD SAYING GOES,

157
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,875
A PERFECT STORM
OF CIRCUMSTANCES.

158
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:32,083
- YOU'RE A MURDERER...

159
00:09:32,166 --> 00:09:34,125
- ( laughs )

160
00:09:34,208 --> 00:09:35,666
- Ryner: YOU SLAUGHTERED
ANY POOR JERK

161
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:38,166
HAPLESS ENOUGH TO
HAVE SEEN THE DRAGON.

162
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:41,500
AND ALL JUST TO KEEP
A USELESS RELIC A SECRET.

163
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:43,916
- Sui: WELL, IT IS EASIER TO
HARNESS A RELIC'S POWER

164
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,208
WHEN YOU'RE NOT WRENCHING
IT FROM THE RABBLE,

165
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:47,291
WHICH, I'M SORRY TO SAY...

166
00:09:47,375 --> 00:09:49,041
INCLUDES THE TWO OF YOU.

167
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:50,708
- IS THAT SUPPOSED
TO BE A THREAT?

168
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,000
- Ferris: WHAT'S YOUR GOAL?

169
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:53,541
EXACTLY WHO AND WHAT

170
00:09:53,625 --> 00:09:56,000
ARE YOU TRYING TO
COLLECT THE RELICS FOR?

171
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,958
- BIT OF AN INVOLVED QUESTION
FOR SOMEONE ABOUT TO DIE.

172
00:09:59,041 --> 00:10:01,333
YOU'RE TRYING TO BUY
TIME, AREN'T YOU?

173
00:10:01,416 --> 00:10:04,250
- PERHAPS... I CAN HARDLY
BE BLAMED FOR IT.

174
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:07,375
FORTUNATELY, IT'S AN EASY ENOUGH
MATTER TO DEDUCE WHAT COUNTRY

175
00:10:07,458 --> 00:10:10,291
YOU'RE AFFILIATED WITH.

176
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:12,916
- I OFFER UP A CONTRACT TO BEAR
THE WICKED SPIRIT BEAST

177
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,666
THAT SLEEPS WITHIN THE EARTH!

178
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:19,583
- A SPELL TO INCREASE
YOUR INNATE PHYSICAL PROWESS?

179
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:21,041
I ADMIRE THE SWIFTNESS...

180
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:23,791
FROM THE WEST I DRAW THE
EMPTY, THE FORMATION, THE YANG!

181
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:26,583
- THE EMPTY, THE FORMATION,
THE YANG!

182
00:10:26,666 --> 00:10:29,250
- AN ALPHA STIGMA!
I SUMMON FORTH THE BRILLIANCE!

183
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:32,166
HE JUMPED MY INVOCATION!
WATCH OUT!

184
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,875
- ( grunting )

185
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:42,791
- CRAP!

186
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:49,916
- IT'S NICE TO KNOW
MY LOOKS DISTRACT YOU

187
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,541
EVEN IN THE MIDST OF BATTLE.

188
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,041
BUT SURELY FOCUSING
ON OUR OPPONENTS

189
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,458
WOULD BE A BETTER TACTIC?

190
00:10:54,541 --> 00:10:55,916
- WHAT THE HELL
IS YOUR PROBLEM?

191
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,291
YOU DO KNOW THESE
FREAKS WANT TO MURDER US.

192
00:10:58,375 --> 00:11:00,750
- NO POINT SURRENDERING
OUR SENSE OF HUMOR.

193
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:02,500
- IS ALL OF THIS A JOKE TO YOU?

194
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:05,000
- NOT THE PART WHERE YOU
DEFLECTED THE AFTERSHOCKS

195
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:07,041
OF A HIT THAT WOULD'VE
OTHERWISE KILLED ME, NO.

196
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:09,791
- ( sighs )

197
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:16,333
RIGHT. SO LOOK OUT
FOR THE SCYTHE.

198
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:18,666
- THAT'S A RELIC TOO THEN,
I TAKE IT?

199
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:21,250
- YEAH. ONE THAT APPEARS
TO RAISE ITS USER'S

200
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:24,166
NATURAL ABILITIES BY A PRETTY
DAMN SIGNIFICANT MARGIN.

201
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,291
- AND...

202
00:11:26,375 --> 00:11:28,250
- WELL, GUESS THAT EXPLAINS
WHY NONE OF THE BODIES

203
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:30,250
SHOWED ANY SIGNS OF TRAUMA.

204
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:33,125
AND WHERE THAT SUDDEN
WALL OF ICE EMERGED FROM.

205
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:36,083
- A SWORD WEIGHED DOWN WITH
ICE GETS TOO HEAVY TO USE...

206
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,750
THAT, AND AS THE
TEMPERATURE PLUMMETS,

207
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,333
IT'S HARDER TO STAY NIMBLE.

208
00:11:39,416 --> 00:11:41,000
- ALRIGHT THEN...

209
00:11:41,083 --> 00:11:43,458
I'LL CREATE AN OPENING
WITH A GOOD OLD FASHIONED

210
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:46,166
BOUT OF FIRE MAGIC AND YOU GET
THE SCYTHE OUT OF HER HANDS.

211
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:47,791
SOUND LIKE A PLAN?

212
00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:50,166
- ONE I'M GLAD TO BE PART OF.

213
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:52,416
- FORMED AN ATTACK
STRATEGY HAVE WE?

214
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,541
- Ryner: YEAH.
YOU MIGHT SAY THAT.

215
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:56,458
- THEN THIS SHOULD BE FUN.

216
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:58,958
IN ALL SERIOUSNESS,
IT'D HARDLY BE WORTH GOUGING

217
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:00,041
THE ALPHA STIGMA OUT OF YOU

218
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:02,291
IF YOU DIDN'T STRUGGLE
A LITTLE BIT...

219
00:12:02,375 --> 00:12:04,458
- WORRY NOT, I'LL CRYSTALLIZE
IT TO KEEP IT IN MINT CONDITION.

220
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:06,625
- CRYSTALLIZE?

221
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:09,416
- OF COURSE. THAT'S HOW AN
ALPHA STIGMA IS CONTAINED.

222
